	<title>Running with volumes inherited multiple times fails with ".../rootfs/dev/log: no such file or directory"</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Running the commands below with Docker 1.1.2 reproduces the issue every time:</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">```
$ docker run -v /dev/log:/dev/log --name test1 centos:centos6 true
$ docker run --volumes-from test1 --name test2 centos:centos6 true
$ docker run --volumes-from test2 --name test3 centos:centos6 true
2014/08/19 15:29:59 Error response from daemon: Cannot start container 4bf2d8a5969c3d9b3893ff6a89d7f8cac96573aca832c5a9b67078783d5f93c8: stat /var/lib/docker/devicemapper/mnt/23cef764aeed262d2118571fe5b211e823380f257824129367ed0f519df50c90/rootfs/dev/log: no such file or directory
```
Expected outcome was that the container would start normally and inherit the `/dev/log` volume.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">This issue does not occur in Docker 1.0.0 so it seems to be a regression.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
